President Obama had a video conference with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan. They discussed the progress made by the National Unity Government in naming candidates for key positions, such as Attorney General and Minister of Interior. President Obama praised President Ghani's commitment to reform, highlighting achievements in government revenues and efforts to combat corruption. They also discussed ways to enhance security cooperation and strengthen the Afghan National Defense and Security Forces. President Ghani's leadership in regional cooperation and reconciliation with the Taliban was acknowledged, with the US expressing support for a peace process that reduces violence and ensures stability in Afghanistan and the region. Both leaders intend to reaffirm international support for Afghanistan's peace and stability at upcoming NATO and EU meetings. They also committed to regular consultations throughout the year to support Afghanistan's governance and security.